# Where the robot model comes from. The description is authored as many split-up
# URDF/xacro source files (links, joints, geometries); xacro processes them into
# one URDF document; robot_state_publisher loads that and publishes it as the
# /robot_description topic. Source is a cream document, xacro a basic block,
# robot_state_publisher a plum node, the topic a cream pill.
...@styles
direction: right

urdf: URDF { class: art; shape: page }
xacro: xacro { class: block }
rsp: robot_state_publisher { class: node }
rd: /robot_description { class: topic }

urdf -> xacro: split-up unprocessed files
xacro -> rsp: single processed URDF
rsp -> rd: URDF data
